  <facts><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Good to know</strong></p>
<p><strong>Hiking trails:</strong> Around 3000 kilometres of trails to explore across Madeira </p>
<p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Mountain terrain. Levadas can be narrow, steep and require sure-footedness. </p>
<p><strong>Best time to go:</strong> Madeira has a mild climate year-round with it cooling off a little in the winter months. </p>
<p><strong>Recommended for:</strong> Regular and experienced walkers</p>
<p><strong>Fly into:</strong> Madeira airport</p>
<p><strong>Fly from:</strong> London Gatwick, London Heathrow, Birmingham, Manchester, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Bristol, Newcastle and Leeds Bradford. </p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Why book a walking holiday to Maderia with Inghams</strong></p>
